    "actor_description": "It tips. One more ounce and the lid is gone-heat rushes up my neck, my vision tightens, and my mouth opens on its own. I can hear my voice getting louder and can't seem to stop it. The anger isn't an opinion anymore; it's a physical force shoving outward, demanding release, turning everything I say into impact.",
